n class=title> Bardic Letter to Illuvite</span><hr size=1> Greetings Freedom fighters,<br>
<br>
Ceescrit my old friend, I am glad to see that you are leading a charge against the &quot;Crossteamers&quot;.   I have thought over your offer to join you in your crusade and become Illuvite, but I cannot.  My loyalty is to Tunare and King Tearis.  I WILL however join your crusade as a Warrior of the Dal Kingdom.  I strive to grow stronger so I might defend our lands from the other races and even the Combine itself.<br>
<br>
Something is major wrong with our race as of lately though.  I noticed a member of the cursed Combine Resurrection in Crushbone and I attacked him with upmost prejudice, after all he WAS a Shadowknight in Elven lands.  Tunarian law, if I remember correctly, is to slay all practicers of evil arts on SITE.  Sadly I see elves hunting with necros, Shadowknights, and non-elf all the time, even get flack back from most when I slay the non-dal in their group, much worse they HEAL these non-elves.<br>
<br>
Amazing, the elven race has little fighting spirit I fear, and you Illuvite seem to be helping us to remember this fighting spirit.   <br>
<br>
Feel free to send a message to me when I am hunting if you are in need of a good warrior to take the hits and such.  We are strong, but we need to get stronger to defend our lands.<br>
<br>
Oh, and a little suggestion.  Give the non-dal a time limit to leave our lands.  So far I've gotten almost 25 non-dal to flee our forest with their tail stuck between their legs without having to lift my sword once.  If they don't leave within this time limit... well THEIR FAIR GAME <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Alas my time is short and I am needing to report back to Firona Vie and try to gain some more seasons so I might be able to use my weapons to their full power.<br>
<br>
<br>
(ooc) I'm still kind of new to these &quot;ez boards&quot; does anyone know HOW to put in those pictures under ones name or use a picture as part of their signature.  I know you do Ceescrit  and you once had a nice picture to <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p>Herious D'Righteous

Emerald/Steel Warrior

"Evil Beware! Herious Keeps a dull blade around to sharpen  upon your skulls!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub45.ezboard.com/utulweyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tulweyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guild Master</span><br> <font color=#660000>(3/14/01 9:44:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Elven Fighting Spirit</span><hr size=1> Thank you for your kind words, brother.<br>
<br>
However, I cannot help but question some of your ideals.<br>
<br>
You rightly mention the following:  "The elven race has little fighting spirit I fear" <br>
<br>
But then advocate this:  "Oh, and a little suggestion. Give the non-dal a time limit to leave our lands. So far I've gotten almost 25 non-dal to flee our forest with their tail stuck between their legs without having to lift my sword once. "<br>
<br>
I don't see much fighting spirit in that.  <br>
<br>
OOC I don't play this game to kindly ask people to leave my forest and then escort them to a zone line.  I might as well go to to a blue server.  I play PvP to fight.  <br>
<br>
IC  I restore the honor of the elves and attempt to restore their image as fearless and brave warriors; not as spineless diplomats.<br>
<br>
Illuvitae<br>
Elven Liberation Leader<br>
Tulweyen Venemus<br>
